triageFlags.title: Credit Score in Sub-Prime Tier
triageFlags.description: The applicant's credit score places them in the Sub-Prime tier, requiring stricter lending criteria.
triageFlags.recommendation: Ensure compliance with stricter criteria for Sub-Prime tier applicants.
triageFlags.reasoning: According to policy, a score of 575 falls into Tier C, necessitating additional scrutiny and adherence to stricter lending rules.

triageFlags.title: Debt-to-Income Ratio Close to Maximum for Tier C
triageFlags.description: The applicant's DTI ratio is close to the maximum allowable for their credit tier.
triageFlags.recommendation: Verify all income and expense details to ensure the DTI calculation is accurate.
triageFlags.reasoning: The DTI ratio is a critical measure of affordability, and being close to the limit indicates potential financial strain.

triageFlags.title: Vehicle Mileage Exceeds Policy Limit
triageFlags.description: The vehicle's mileage exceeds the maximum allowed by policy.
triageFlags.recommendation: Consider the impact of high mileage on the vehicle's value and resale potential.
triageFlags.reasoning: High mileage can significantly affect the vehicle's residual value and the overall risk of the loan.

content.reasoning: The identified issues, while not deal-breaking, indicate a higher risk profile. The credit score and DTI ratio suggest financial strain, and the vehicle's mileage exceeds policy limits, potentially affecting resale value.
